Fun fact about yokai:
They either hate foreigners especially or think they look funny and laugh hysterically.
Situation:
You encounter a Korean weeping woman. This is the faceless ghost in the form of a woman usually near water, and appears before you in seclusion so that she can feed upon your soul. It is a vengeful spirit, which expects to feed off of your humanity by you breaking it's "rules" and trying to help it.
She drags you down under the water and drowns you while feeding you her hair once you realize her face looks like a melted painting (in most versions)
However. You've got white skin blonde hair and blue eyes.
You don't fit in, not even a little bit.
So instead she starts laughing so hard she goes back to the spirit realm. Word-of-mouth storytelling and anecdotes would suggest this is the more common occurrence.
Alternate ending she kills you because you're a foreigner and there's no way you know the "rules" so you're easy prey.
